=head1 DESCRIPTION

Specifies an action that Batch will take after the job has remained at
the head of the queue in the specified state for longer than the
specified time.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Action => Str

The action to take when a job is at the head of the job queue in the
specified state for the specified period of time. The only supported
value is C<CANCEL>, which will cancel the job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> MaxTimeSeconds => Int

The approximate amount of time, in seconds, that must pass with the job
in the specified state before the action is taken. The minimum value is
600 (10 minutes) and the maximum value is 86,400 (24 hours).


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Reason => Str

The reason to log for the action being taken.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> State => Str

The state of the job needed to trigger the action. The only supported
value is C<RUNNABLE>.



